items.badge_description: While spontaneity can be fun, sometimes you want to make sure your adventure will rock. Checkout the menu at an Untappd Verified Venue before visiting and know exactly what’s on tap! That's 155 check-ins at venue that is verified. Try 5 more for Level 32!

Want to enjoy a day of brews, but need to keep your wits sharp? There are plenty of delicious brews under 5% for you to sip on throughout the day. That's 55 different beers with an ABV of 5% and lower. Try 5 more for Level 12!
It’s been a long day and now it’s time for a reward. Crisp, tasty and refreshing, enjoy that delicious fruit beer! That's 35 different fruited beers. Try 5 more for Level 8!

Right about now you’re feeling your face tighten and your taste buds explode. The full pucker is quickly setting in and you can’t get enough. This is the wonder of the sour. That's 170 different Sour Beers. Try 5 more for Level 35.

Round and round the wheel goes! Which style you’ll be drinking, nobody knows! Your desire to explore different styles is inspiring. Keep it up! That's a check-in to at least 120 different styles. Try 5 more for Level 25!

beer.beer_description:

items.badge_description: Planning on calling out tomorrow? If not, we’ll be sure to have some coffee ready for you! Drink 5 beers during the week after 10PM (to midnight).
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 50 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 11! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 70 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 15!
Ahh, the trusty pale ale; crisp, refreshing, and always a good choice in a bind. That's 15 different Pale Ales or American Pale Wheats. Try 5 more for Level 4.

Marshmallow, chocolate, apple pie! Cakes and cookies catch my eye. Churn that butter, twist and shout. Put it in a pastry stout! That’s 5 different beers with the style of Stout - Pastry, Stout - Imperial / Double Pastry, or Sour - Smoothie / Pastry. Check-in to 5 more to get to Level 2.
Do you come from the land down under, where beer does flow, and men chunder? That's at least 110 different beers from Australia. Try 5 more for Level 23.

beer.beer_description:
Mango Fizz

Its fizzy, its bubbly, its mango.

Just drink it.

Let me tell you, our brewer has worked his magic with this little number. Loaded with oats, lactose and copious amounts of hops, both in the kettle and dry hop! This beauty will have you searching for your next sip.
This beer is for sipping on while laying out under the stars in the warm nights. Utilises cryo hops and some special whirlpool additions!

Is there anything cooler than flipping your pillow on a hot and sticky night.
Soft Mouthfeel, slightly sweet wit the fruity hop character.  
#Crackasquinters

Schooners & Cans available now of our newest brew! This little beauty packs a nice punch of flavour and jabs your tastebuds right in the sweet spot ?
One, two…one, two, three or four…you’ll love to go round after round with your mates on this one…responsibly of course…

Safe to say the boys found Frothy’s enthusiasm toward this one a little annoying while trying to work ?

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
WELL HOWDY BEER LOVERS, BEST HIDE THIS FROM THE VARMINTS! 
CRACK A WHIP OR A CAN, SIT BACK AND LET THE SUN SET OVER THE PRAIRIE
Double dry hopped IPA
Choc-Caramel Macadamia Stout
A chocolate milk stout with honeycomb

BRUISED EGO ?‼️??
Oat Cream IPA
6.4% abv

Not exactly what you were expecting but you know what, you kinda liked it…coconut & guava notes combined with a smooth mouthfeel, rich haze and refreshing aroma will make this one a surprising favourite everytime you take a sip!

Nothing like that feeling of unzipping your tent in the morning after a truly awful night sleep on the cold hard ground out in nature, not a proper first world amenity in sight, wondering how on earth you are going to survive another 3 days of this and what horrible dehydrated meal you’ll be consuming for breakfast lunch and dinner…

Well we have a solution…
Take a few ‘Happy Campers’ along with you from Squinters Brewing Co and you might just find you enjoy the trip that little bit more ? 

A delicious hoppy pale ale, perfect for any occasion where good beer and good times are required ??
Enjoy this new brew and don’t forget to be a ‘Happy Camper’….

Now this one is extra special…

We took our Dark Smooth Stout and brewed two identical batches, adding Belgium Candy Syrup to boost the booze, flavour and mouth feel. We aged the first batch in imported Bourbon Barrels for ten months and the second batch in Australian Whiskey Barrels for six months then carefully blended it all together to create this absolutely delicious winter brew.

If you like warm hugs by the fireplace then this one’s for you. Come down to Squinters to try it straight from the tap or take some home and enjoy however you see fit.

Our little brewer sure loves BIG flavour and BIG stouts ?? Good job on this one Jar!!
Delicious triple choc stout. Sweet
Maple marshmallow chocolate stout.

You know those summer days, late in the afternoon, when you look up in the sky and see a beautiful golden sunset…yeah? Okay well, now imagine someone climbed up a ladder to the heavens, reached up and scooped all that goldenness into a glass and served it right in front of you…
Sounds pretty good huh…
So we didn’t quite do that, too many logistics etc, but we got pretty damn close!
So next time you find yourself looking up at one one of those, slide on a pair of aviators, run your fingers through your hair, put some 80’s ballad on your stereo and just sip back and enjoy this easy drinking delicious treat the masterminds at Squinters Brewing Co created, just for you!
